---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — ToolOrbit"
  description="ToolOrbit's privacy policy: what data is and isn't collected, why every tool processes data client-side, and what analytics are in use."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-base-50 sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-base-400">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-base-200 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-base-50">
          How the tools process your data
        </h2>
        <p>
          Every tool on ToolOrbit runs entirely client-side, in your browser, using standard
          JavaScript and Web APIs (such as the Web Crypto API for hashing). The text, files, or
          values you enter into a tool are never uploaded, transmitted to, or stored on any
          ToolOrbit server. Once you close or navigate away from a tool's page, whatever you
          entered is gone — nothing was sent anywhere to begin with.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-base-50">What we do collect</h2>
        <p>
          ToolOrbit uses privacy-respecting analytics (Cloudflare Web Analytics) to understand
          aggregate traffic — which pages are visited, roughly how many people use the site, and
          basic technical details like browser type. This analytics method does not use cookies
          and does not track individuals across sites. We do not run third-party tracking
          scripts, fingerprinting, or cross-site advertising pixels.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-base-50">Local storage</h2>
        <p>
          Some preferences — like your dark/light theme choice — are saved in your browser's
          local storage so they persist between visits. This data stays on your device and is
          never transmitted to ToolOrbit or any third party.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-base-50">Advertising</h2>
        <p>
          ToolOrbit may display ads in the future to cover hosting costs. If and when ads are
          added, this policy will be updated with full disclosure of which ad network is used and
          what data it collects, before any ads go live.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="mb-2 font-display text-lg font-semibold text-base-50">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy can be sent through the <a
            href="/contact"
            class="text-interactive hover:underline">contact page</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
